<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    PUF France Use Case 25: Single-Purpose Voucher (BUU) Sale Invoice

    Business Scenario:
    - ISSUER (entertainment venue) sells single-purpose vouchers (bons à usage unique) to a B2B buyer
    - The voucher grants access to 50 concert performances at a specific venue
    - Since the place of supply, VAT base, rate, and territoriality are all determined at issuance,
      this is classified as a BUU (Bon à Usage Unique)
    - VAT is due at each transfer of a BUU

    Key UC25 BUU Concepts:
    - BUU: Place of supply + VAT known at issuance → VAT charged at sale
    - Sale to a taxable person (assujetti) → e-invoicing
    - Sale to an individual → e-reporting (not shown here)
    - If Issuer = Supplier: redemption is NOT a separate taxable event
    - If Issuer ≠ Supplier: supplier invoices issuer at redemption (see companion example)
    - Commissions/fees must be invoiced separately (not on this invoice)

    VAT Treatment:
    - VAT chargeability for services: at receipt of payment for the voucher
    - Standard 20% VAT applies (entertainment services at a known venue)
    - This invoice IS the taxable event for BUU

    Source: XP Z12-014 Annexe A v1.3, Section 3.2.24.1
    Note: This use case is still under discussion and subject to significant additions.
-->
<Invoice xmlns="urn:pagero:PageroUniversalFormat:Invoice:1.0" xmlns:cac="urn:pagero:CommonAggregateComponents:1.0" xmlns:cbc="urn:oasis:names:specification:ubl:schema:xsd:CommonBasicComponents-2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:puf="urn:pagero:ExtensionComponent:1.0" xmlns:ext="urn:oasis:names:specification:ubl:schema:xsd:CommonExtensionComponents-2">

    <!-- BT-24 Specification identifier -->
    <cbc:CustomizationID>urn:pagero.com:puf:billing:2.0</cbc:CustomizationID>
    <!-- BT-23 Business process type -->
    <cbc:ProfileID>urn:pagero.com:puf:billing:1.0</cbc:ProfileID>
    <!-- BT-1 Invoice Number -->
